============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the Magna Carta?
A1: The Magna Carta (1215) was a charter limiting royal
     power in England, establishing that the king is subject
     to law. It influenced modern constitutional law and
     human rights.

Q2: What is osmosis?
A2: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q3: What is the Renaissance?
A3: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q4: What is artificial intelligence?
A4: AI is the simulation of human intelligence by machines,
     including learning, reasoning, and problem-solving.
     Types: narrow AI (specific tasks) and general AI
     (human-level across domains).

Q5: What is entropy?
A5: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     HIV/AIDS
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HIV
Transmission:Sexual contact, blood
Symptoms:    Flu-like; then AIDS symptoms
Treatment:   Antiretroviral therapy (ART)
Deaths/yr:   0.65M
Vaccine:     No (in development)
Discovered:  1983

Disease:     Tuberculosis
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    M. tuberculosis
Transmission:Airborne droplets
Symptoms:    Persistent cough, night sweats
Treatment:   6-9 month antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   1.6M
Vaccine:     Yes (BCG, partial)
Discovered:  1882

Disease:     Ebola
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Ebola virus
Transmission:Bodily fluids contact
Symptoms:    Fever, bleeding, organ failure
Treatment:   Monoclonal antibodies, supportive
Deaths/yr:   0.001M
Vaccine:     Yes (Ervebo for Zaire strain)
Discovered:  1976

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

